      "writtenOn": "2019-08-22T19:56:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. const-qualify, because you don’t want outsiders modifying object-internal data.\n\n2. Type as uint8_t* since that’s what you’re storing it as.\n\n3. Outside of the context of “GetAllData()”, which isn’t even right next to this, it’s not clear whether this applies to the last write or to all writes, just by name alone as you’d see it at a call site.\n\nSuggestion: GetLastWrittenData() and GetAllData().",
      "revId": "80b63241e38520fee059cf093ba887a0f4ad56dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
