      "writtenOn": "2019-08-22T19:56:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Will this ever be used independently of GetLastWrittenData()? Seems like it might not be. In that case, just do:\n\n  const uint8_t* GetLastWrittenData(size_t* size) const;\n\nAlternative, using object orientation and the standard library to your advantage:\n\n  const std::vector\u003cuint8_t\u003e\u0026 GetLastWrittenData() const;\n\nFor more hints favoring the vector implementation (regardless of how you provide the interface here), see my comments in the .cc file.\n\nIf you do need to maintain this as an independent method, adapt its name consistent with the previous comment.\n\nSame applies on line 46.",
      "revId": "80b63241e38520fee059cf093ba887a0f4ad56dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
